GRANT Example

Give SELECT permission on ashokdb to user sunil:

GRANT SELECT
ON ashokdb
TO sunil;

Give SELECT and INSERT permissions:

GRANT SELECT, INSERT
ON ashokdb
TO sunil;

Give all permissions:

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES
ON ashokdb
TO sunil;


///////////////////

REVOKE Example

Remove INSERT permission:

REVOKE INSERT
ON ashokdb
FROM sunil;

Remove both SELECT and INSERT permissions:

REVOKE SELECT, INSERT
ON ashokdb
FROM sunil;

Remove all permissions:

REVOKE ALL PRIVILEGES
ON ashokdb
FROM sunil;

.....................................


Real-Time Example

Suppose you have an employee table:

CREATE TABLE Employee (
    eid INT,
    ename VARCHAR(50),
    salary DECIMAL(10,2)
);

Create a user:

CREATE USER 'empuser' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

Allow only viewing data:

GRANT SELECT
ON Employee
TO empuser;

Now empuser can run:

SELECT * FROM Employee;

But cannot run:

INSERT INTO Employee VALUES (1,'Sunil',50000);

Later, if you want to remove even the viewing permission:

REVOKE SELECT
ON Employee
FROM empuser;
